{
  "stem": "8784.1",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "I was simply living in total fear.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And during the night, when I slept on the workbench, the fear drove me absolutely insane.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "At times, I could've swore that somebody was knocking on my window.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And all it was is a little kitten sitting on the outside of the window.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "But that drove me nuts, thinking that somebody's trying to break into the workshop.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "I simply-- I simply lived with fear.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And when I could no longer stand it, I eventually went into the ghetto together with my family.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "So sometimes in 1941, I went into the ghetto with my-- and joined my family.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "We wound up in the ghetto, the family of us, of six children, parents wound up in the ghetto.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "Because we came into the ghetto very late, the housing facilities were no longer readily available, maybe as they were before.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we were-- as a family of eight, we were assigned a room in a basement.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I remember that basement room.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "It was a horrible condition living there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But that's all we could get.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Food was in very short supply.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Hygiene facilities were nonexistent, or not to speak of anyway.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "You could not get a night's rest, because people were working at odd hours and coming back.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And living eight people in one room just did not let us rest too much.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But nevertheless, in, in truth, if I had to recall it, what we felt like, when we came into the ghetto, we somehow felt relieved that we are now amongst our own people and maybe the situation will be a little better than living outside of the ghetto and living in fear.",
      "word_count": 52
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So for a while, we, we thought, well, this is great.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
